                <head>75. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Following the meeting at 5 p.m. on the Austrian State Treaty (see <ref
                        target="#d73">Document 73</ref>), the Foreign Ministers of the United
                    Kingdom, the Soviet Union, and France attended a dinner given by Secretary of
                    State <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName> at Ambassador <persName
                        corresp="#p_TLE1">Thompson</persName>’s residence. In the course of their
                    conversation during and after the dinner the Foreign Ministers discussed Formosa
                    and a Four-Power Conference at some length and Indochina, disarmament, and the
                    Berlin Autobahn tax briefly. For a report on the discussion of Formosa and a
                    Four-Power Conference, see <ref target="#d116">Document 116</ref>; memoranda of
                    the other conversations are in Department of State, Conference Files: Lot 60 D
                    627, CF 445.</p>
            </div>
